Skip to main content









              Blue Capital Management Ltd.          






          Blue Capital Management Ltd.    







 






Blue Capital Management Ltd. ("Blue Capital") provides innovative catastrophe reinsurance-linked investment products for institutional and retail investors. Blue Capital is the wholly-owned asset management platform of Endurance Specialty Holdings Ltd., a member of the Sompo International group of companies and a wholly-owned subsidiary of Sompo Holdings, Inc. Sompo International is a recognized global specialty provider of property and casualty insurance and reinsurance and a leader in property catastrophe and short tail reinsurance since 2001.
By leveraging Sompo International’s underwriting expertise and deep broker and client relationships, Blue Capital differentiates itself by providing investors broad access to the global catastrophe reinsurance market.
 





Asset Management
Alternative asset management focused exclusively on insurance-linked assets offering a range of risk opportunities with attractive investor returns.
 
 

Listed Vehicles
U.K. and U.S. publicly-listed vehicles invested in select catastrophe reinsurance risks which are largely uncorrelated to other asset classes.
Blue Capital Alternative Investment Fund Limited (LSE:BCAI) Blue Capital Reinsurance Holdings Ltd. (NYSE: BCRH)
 



Custom Products
Investment strategies in the global property catastrophe market can be customized to meet the objectives and risk tolerances of qualified institutional investors. Our products include Open Funds, Funds of One and Private Sidecars.
 

Collateralized Reinsurance
Fully collateralized reinsurance protection for the property catastrophe insurance and reinsurance markets is offered through Blue Water Re.
 
 


















Directors & Management | Blue Capital



























Skip to main content









              Blue Capital Management Ltd.          






          Blue Capital Management Ltd.    







 




Directors & Management



John Del Col Director
John V. Del Col serves as a Director of Blue Capital Management Ltd. and has been the General Counsel and Secretary of Endurance Specialty Holdings Ltd., a wholly owned subsidiary of Sompo Holdings, Inc. Prior to joining Endurance in January 2003, Mr. Del Col was General Counsel and Deputy General Counsel for several property and casualty reinsurers and a merchant bank, having begun his career in associate roles at several New York law firms. He holds a JD from Harvard University and an AB from Dartmouth College. He is admitted to practice law in New York State.
 
Mike McGuire Director
Michael J. McGuire is the Director of Blue Capital Management Ltd. and Chairman of the Board for Blue Capital Reinsurance Holdings Ltd. He has served as Chief Financial Officer of Endurance Specialty Holdings Ltd., a wholly owned subsidiary of Sompo Holdings, Inc., since January 2006. Prior to this role, he led Endurance’s external reporting, treasury and Sarbanes-Oxley compliance initiatives from 2003 through 2006. Mr. McGuire has a broad range of public accounting experience in audit and advisory roles in the United States, Bermuda and Europe, which included providing transaction accounting, structuring and due diligence services to private equity and strategic investors on mergers and acquisitions. Mr. McGuire is a Certified Public Accountant and a member of the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants.
 
Carrie Rosorea Director
Carrie Rosorea serves as a Director of Blue Capital Management Ltd. and has served as Chief Accounting Officer of Endurance Specialty Holdings Ltd., a wholly owned subsidiary of Sompo Holdings, Inc. since February 2013. Ms. Rosorea joined Endurance in 2005 and has held several financial reporting and controller positions of increasing responsibility, most recently Executive Vice President and Corporate Controller. From October 2000 to April 2005, Ms. Rosorea served as a Controller at Alta Partners, a San Francisco-based private equity firm. Previously, she worked as an Assistant Controller at XL Mid Ocean Reinsurance Company Ltd. and as a Senior Accountant in the audit practice of Deloitte & Touche LLP, both in the United States and Bermuda. Ms. Rosorea is a Certified Public Accountant.
 
Greg Garside Treasurer
Greg Garside is Treasurer of Blue Capital Management Ltd. and Chief Financial Officer of Blue Capital Reinsurance Holdings Ltd.  Greg also serves as Controller and Vice President of Endurance Specialty Holdings Ltd., a wholly owned subsidiary of Sompo Holdings, Inc. Prior to joining Endurance, he served as Assistant Controller at LaSalle Re Ltd. and worked in the insurance audit practice at KPMG in Bermuda. Previously, Mr. Garside was a trainee accountant at Moore Stephens Chartered Accountants in London. Mr. Garside is a member of the Institute of Chartered Accountants in England and Wales.
 
William Haddrell Portfolio Manager
William Haddrell is the Portfolio Manager, responsible for risk origination, underwriting and trading, and has worked at Blue Capital since December 2013. Prior to his current role, he worked for Hardy Bermuda within the property treaty team as an underwriter with a focus on the USA and Japan. Prior to Hardy Bermuda William Haddrell worked as an underwriter in the direct and facultative team at Renaissance Re’s Syndicate 1458 at Lloyd’s of London from 2010-2013 and as an underwriting analyst for Renaissance Re Bermuda from 2008-2010.
 
Allison Kiene
SVP, Assistant General Counsel & Chief Compliance Officer
Allison Kiene is Secretary and Chief Compliance Officer of Blue Capital Management Ltd. She is also Senior Vice President and Assistant General Counsel for Endurance Services. Ms. Kiene joined Montpelier Re Holdings Ltd. (acquired by Endurance Specialty Holdings Ltd. in July 2015) in October 2007. Prior to joining Montpelier, Ms. Kiene served as Senior Vice President, General Counsel and Corporate Secretary for Familymeds Group Inc. Ms. Kiene is admitted to the Bar in Connecticut, Massachusetts and New York.
 


















